articles.author: Nidal Al-Mughrabi
articles.description: Israel pursued its military operation in Gaza after it agreed to lift a two-month-old blockade on aid deliveries that has left the enclave on the brink of famine.
articles.title: Israel kills 20 Palestinians in airstrikes after agreeing to let some aid into Gaza

articles.author: Guy Faulconbridge, Lidia Kelly
articles.description: Trump said he would also speak to Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskiy and various members of NATO.
articles.title: Trump to speak to Putin on end to war in Ukraine as Europeans demand ceasefire

articles.author: Alistair Smout, Andrew Macaskill, Andrew Gray
articles.description: Britain agreed the most significant reset of defence and trade ties with the European Union since Brexit on Monday after U.S. President Donald Trump's upending of the global order pushed the two sides to move on from their acrimonious divorce.
articles.title: UK strikes EU trade and defence reset in 'new era' for relations

articles.author: Andrew Chung
articles.description: The U.S. Supreme Court allowed Donald Trump's administration on Monday to strip about 350,000 Venezuelans living in the United States of a temporary protected status given under his predecessor Joe Biden, as the Republican president moves to ramp up deportations as part of his hardline approach to immigration.
articles.title: US Supreme Court lets Trump end deportation protection for Venezuelans

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Donald Trump and Vladimir Putin spoke by telephone on Monday, the third officially announced call this year between the presidents of the United States and Russia.
articles.title: What to know about the Trump-Putin call on Ukraine

articles.author: David Lawder, Promit Mukherjee, Julia Payne
articles.description: Finance leaders from the Group of Seven democracies will strive for a show of unity when they meet this week on topics other than U.S. President Donald Trump's tariffs, including economic security, Ukraine and artificial intelligence cooperation.
articles.title: G7 finance leaders to seek US consensus on non-tariff issues at Canada meeting

articles.author: John Kruzel
articles.description: The U.S. Supreme Court in a trio of rulings expected in the coming weeks appears inclined to extend its trend of taking an expansive view of religious rights while potentially dealing a sharp blow to the principle of separation of church and state.
articles.title: US Supreme Court may broaden religious rights in looming rulings

articles.author: Nidal Al-Mughrabi, Alexander Cornwell, Maayan Lubell
articles.description: For more than a year, Israeli authorities prevented Ayed Ayoub from escaping Gaza's hunger and war with his family for an academic fellowship in France. He finally left last month, after Israel unexpectedly eased its tight control of the border.
articles.title: Trump plan or not, Israel is letting more Palestinians leave Gaza

articles.author: Nate Raymond
articles.description: Lawyers for a Guatemalan man who says he was deported to Mexico despite his fears he would be persecuted there have asked a judge to order the Trump administration to immediately facilitate his return after immigration officials acknowledged making a mistake in his case.
articles.title: Lawyers seek to force Trump to return Guatemalan deportee

articles.author: Khalid Abdelaziz, Eltayeb Siddig
articles.description: The bespectacled, grey-bearded man ran out of the primary school in Khartoum's Amarat district, shaking with shock.
articles.title: Families find a new danger in Sudan's battered capital, unexploded shells
